### OpenCode custom commands (this repo)

Commands live under `.opencode/commands/*.md` (names match OpenCode slash commands):

| Command file | Purpose |
|--------------|---------|
| `daily.md` | Daily automation / hygiene workflow |
| `setup.md` | Environment / project setup |
| `welcome.md` | Onboarding / context primer |
| `wave-runner.md`, `wave-status.md`, `wave-tui.md` | Wave runner batch execution (TUI-related) |
| `omo-shortcuts.md`, `omo-status.md` | Oh-My-OpenCode shortcuts and status |

**OpenCode `instructions`:** `opencode.json` loads `.opencode/rules/exarp-go.md`, `lint-after-generation.md`, `regression-sanity.md`, `derive-builder-pattern.md`, `shared-types-pattern.md`, `context-compression.md`. **Cursor parity:** `.cursor/rules/` includes matching ideas — `lint-generated-files.mdc`, `regression-sanity.mdc`, `context-compression.mdc`, plus `workspace-build-before-commit.mdc`, `stub-must-have-task.mdc`, `no-new-duplicate-types.mdc`, `keep-type-comparison-docs.mdc`, `work-without-xcode.mdc`; `derive_builder` / shared types remain canonical in `AGENTS.md` and `.opencode/rules/*.md`.

### Cursor custom commands

Project commands: `.cursor/commands.json` (e.g. `build`, `test:run`, `lint:run`, `git:pull-safe`, MLX/Ollama review). See `docs/CURSOR_PROJECT_COMMANDS.md` if present.

### Skills & subagents

| Consumer | Context source | Notes |
|----------|----------------|-------|
| Cursor / plugin skills | AGENTS.md, relevant quick reference, `.cursor/rules/` | Use Skill tool; project root = workspace root |
| Subagents (mcp_task, exarp-go, Claude agents) | Pass in prompt: project root + “Canonical guidelines: AGENTS.md plus the relevant quick reference” | They do not auto-load workspace context |

Full setup and command parity: [docs/archive/AI_EDITOR_SETUP.md](docs/archive/AI_EDITOR_SETUP.md). exarp-go across Cursor, Claude, OpenCode, Codex: [docs/archive/EXARP_GO_CURSOR_CLAUDE_OPENCODE.md](docs/archive/EXARP_GO_CURSOR_CLAUDE_OPENCODE.md).

### Which rule when

| When working with | Use rule | Purpose |
|-------------------|----------|---------|
| C++ source/headers | `cpp-source.mdc` | Style, financial code standards |
| C++ tests | `cpp-tests.mdc` | Catch2 conventions |
| Python | `python-code.mdc` | Style, uv, pytest |
| Automation / Todo2 / docs health | `project-automation.mdc`, `automation-tool-suggestions.mdc` | exarp-go, task alignment |
| Canonical context, skills, subagents | `ai-editors-skills-subagents.mdc`, docs/archive/AI_EDITOR_SETUP.md | AGENTS.md plus CLAUDE.md / CODEX.md, multi-editor setup |
| Context compression | `context-compression.mdc` | When to compress at workflow milestones (see `.opencode/rules/context-compression.md`) |
| Rust workspace commit / types / stubs | `workspace-build-before-commit.mdc`, `no-new-duplicate-types.mdc`, `stub-must-have-task.mdc`, `keep-type-comparison-docs.mdc` | Same intent as `.opencode/rules/*.md` |
| macOS without Xcode CLI | `work-without-xcode.mdc` | Limited verification path until `cc` works |
| Documentation references | `documentation.mdc` | @docs, global docs |
| Git / pre-commit / exarp-go hooks | `hooks.mdc` | pre-commit, setup_pre_commit_hook.sh, setup_hooks |
| Security before code gen | `semgrep.mdc` | security_check |
| Rule index | `rules-index.mdc` | List of all rules and when to use each |

### Cursor Glob Rules

| Rule | Glob | Purpose |
|------|------|---------|
| `cpp-source.mdc` | `native/src/**/*.cpp`, `native/include/**/*.h` | C++ style, financial code standards |
| `cpp-tests.mdc` | `native/tests/**/*.cpp` | Catch2 test conventions |
| `python-code.mdc` | `python/**/*.py` | Python style, uv, pytest |

## Context Hierarchy

1. **`AGENTS.md`** — Authoritative source of project guidelines
2. **`CLAUDE.md` / `CODEX.md`** — Claude Code and Codex quick references (Rust workspace path, build commands)
3. **Tool-specific files** — Add invocation hints, not duplicate policy
4. **`.cursor/rules/`** — Context-specific rules with glob patterns
5. **`.claude/agents/`** — Specialized sub-agents for repeated workflows

## When Adding New Context

1. **Prefer updating existing files** over creating new ones
2. **Reference AGENTS.md** instead of duplicating content
3. **Keep tool-specific files minimal** — only add unique hints
4. **Add glob patterns** to `.cursor/rules/` for file-type specific guidance

## Quick Reference

For AI agents working on this project:
- Start with `AGENTS.md` for complete guidelines
- Use `CODEX.md` or `CLAUDE.md` only as the quick reference for that tool
- Check `.cursor/rules/` for context-specific rules
- Use MCP tools via `.cursor/mcp.json` configuration
- Use Claude agents for specialized workflows (test writing, trading review, refactoring)
